have any questions, please call the Republic News Desk at (602)
444-8286.
<TEXT>
<P>
   &QL; 
WIRELESS _ The entrance of Sprint Broadband, available at the
moment only in the Valley, makes Phoenix one of the few proving
grounds in the nation where the three leading broadband
technologies _ cable, telephone digital subscriber lines and fixed
wireless _ go head to head for the residential and small-business
market. Story will move in the ``A'' and ``F'' categories.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
STADIUM _ The Diamondbacks want to shut the only door _ albeit, a
back entrance _ through which the public can access detailed
information about the team's finances. Team executives said the
Diamondbacks want an exemption from a contract that requires the
privately held Diamondbacks to give the public a peek at the team's
bottom line, debt, cash flow and even Managing Partner Jerry
Colangelo's seven-figure fee. Story will move in the ``A''
category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
WILLIAMS _ Mesa's Williams Gateway Airport, where thousands of Air
Force pilots earned their wings, is now facing its ultimate test:
shedding the last of its drab military fatigues to become a modern
passenger airport. Now, Williams' ambitious plan to become an East
Valley passenger alternative to Phoenix's Sky Harbor International
Airport has run into some serious turbulence. Story will move in
the ``A'' category. &QL; 
