<SLUG> BC-SOC-CHINA-GUATEMALA-BOS </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
CHINA CRUISES 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
 By JIM GREENIDGE  
 c.2000 The Boston Globe  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   FOXBOROUGH, Mass. _ For 20 minutes, it was a game. Guatemala
kept the powerful Chinese from scoring a goal. In the 21st minute,
however, it broke down.
</P>
<P>
   China won the opening-round game in the Women's Gold Cup at
Foxboro Stadium, 14-0, Saturday. And that was without Chinese star
Sun Wen, who is sidelined by a knee injury.
</P>
<P>
   ``Everybody made a good effort in the first 20 minutes,'' said
Guatemala coach Graco Lopez. ``The game is 90 minutes, though. We
were out there trying, but we've got to do it for the full 90
minutes.
</P>
<P>
   ``This game was a learning experience. We were lacking in our
offense, but I thought for 20 minutes, things seemed to be rather
positive.''
</P>
<P>
   Jin Yan scored China's first two goals _ in the 21st and 26th
minutes. Zhang Ouying notched four goals and four assists while
teammate Shui Qingxia had three goals as China unloaded 45 shots.
</P>
<P>
   The inexperienced Guatemalans took one shot the entire game, a
Claudia Galvez lob from 25 yards out that Chinese goalkeeper Gao
Hong handled with ease.
</P>
<P>
   ``We would have liked to have had more offense,'' said Lopez,
whose team is still in the organizational stages. ``We knew what to
expect. We knew it would be a difficult game. They were a lot
faster than we were.''
</P>
<P>
   Guatemalan netminder Susana De Leon made 15 saves, nine in the
first half.
</P>
<P>
   ``I really thought it would be difficult, though,'' said De
Leon, who twisted her left ankle in the 31st minute but continued
to play. ``I thought it would be harder. They took a lot of shots
from a distance, but they were real fast, though.''
</P>
<P>
   China coach Ma Yuanan liked his team's effort _ even in the
first 20 minutes. ``Soccer's a game that's quite exciting, and it's
attacking as well,'' he said through a translator. ``That's what we
were doing in those first 20 minutes. We did take our chances over
that time. We did throughout the game.
</P>
<P>
   ``I thought without Sun Wen it would be more entertaining. This
was kind of a warmup for us. We played hard every minute and we
played in order to have success.''
</P>
<P>
   Monday, Mexico plays Guatemala and China meets Canada in
Hershey, Pa., in this Group B round robin. China and Canada met
June 8 in the Pacific Cup, tying, 2-2, in regulation, with Canada
winning on penalty kicks.
</P>
<P>
   Ma would not discuss the possibility of a rubber game with the
United States _ China beat the United States, 1-0, May 31 in the
opening round of the Pacific Cup; the United States beat China on
penalty kicks in the World Cup last July.
</P>
<P>
   ``I will give you my opinion if we meet (the US); that would be
after the game,'' he said. ``It's hard to make it clear now. I'll
see you after the final for the answer.''
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
